2. LinkedIn (linkedin.com)
Purpose: Professional networking, internship applications, and industry connections.
LinkedIn is used by recruiters, HR professionals, and companies worldwide to find talent. I filled in my Education section with:

Degree: B.Tech in Computer Science Engineering
Institution: VIT Bhopal University
Expected Graduation Year: 2029

3. Kaggle (kaggle.com)
Purpose: Data science competitions, datasets, and machine learning learning paths.
Kaggle is the largest data science community platform in the world. It hosts competitions, open datasets, and beginner-friendly notebooks. Even at this early stage in my degree, creating an account allows me to follow notebooks, explore datasets, and prepare for the data science and ML modules in later semesters.

Reflection 
For this task, I set up accounts on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle — three platforms that together cover the full arc of a computer science student's professional development.
GitHub is the most immediately relevant for my degree: almost every coding project, assignment, or open-source contribution I make over the next four years will be stored and showcased here. Having a profile README from Day 1 means I am building my professional identity alongside my technical skills, rather than scrambling to put something together in my final year.
LinkedIn felt more distant at first — I do not yet have internship experience or projects to list — but I quickly realised that the platform rewards early starters. Connections made now with seniors, alumni, and faculty can open doors that are much harder to access later.
Kaggle was the most exciting to discover. I had heard of data science competitions but did not realise how structured the learning resources were. I plan to complete Kaggle's free Python and Data Visualisation micro-courses in my first year, which will complement my academic curriculum.
Setting up these three profiles together has given me a clear picture of the digital professional ecosystem — and a concrete plan for how to use it over the next four years.
